Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:02.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Buccaneer guy's automail made differently?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.26,0:02:06.77,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good, Doc. I can't get this helmet off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:09.02,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That's my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.94,0:02:17.53,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,All automail here must be made to be flexible, lightweight, and resistant to cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.11,0:02:25.04,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,So through trial and error, an automail made with duralumin, carbon fiber, nickel, and copper was developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:29.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was just made of iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:31.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder I couldn't destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.13,0:02:36.26,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Doc, you're not planning on spilling all the beans, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.26,0:02:37.55,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Why, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:40.38,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,He's a famous State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.30,0:02:42.68,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure he's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.89,0:02:45.68,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,He has the silver pocketwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.27,0:02:49.48,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A guy like this is of equal standing to a major?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:55.94,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,If you're planning on staying up north for a while, you should switch to a cold climate automail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.19,0:02:58.19,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Where does your automail mechanic work?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:00.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Rush Valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:05.12,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,They knew a customer was heading up north and didn't even bother to tell you the dangers or offer a replacement?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:09.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I didn't tell her that I was going to be up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:15.00,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to die, you need to get it replaced;\Neven if it means your mechanic has to take a trip here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:17.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:19.51,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 100 cenz for the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.97,0:03:22.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What a cheap trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.63,0:03:25.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And this coffee tastes worse than the one at Eastern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:26.76,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Your fault for letting your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.10,0:03:32.27,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,So? What did you come here to do with that normal automail of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:34.40,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Coming along without even passing through Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:35.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:39.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We came here with a letter of introduction to see if Major General Armstrong could help us out,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:44.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,but that general didn't even listen to me and was\Nblabbering on about how she'd pluck my antenna off...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:47.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Did you call, little brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.99,0:03:49.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"L-Little"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:50.33,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:52.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got something to say, just say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:54.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,M-My hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.42,0:04:04.01,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I look ridiculous...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.56,0:04:15.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So... I hear you're on good terms with my little brother, Alex.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:17.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Is he doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:19.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.27,0:04:21.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,As muscular as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:22.90,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,He's as cheerful as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:25.57,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,"Tch"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.12,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Nevermind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Moving right along, tell me why you came to see me without going through Headquarters first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:34.87,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget to include why that armor is empty, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:40.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually... something I don't want a lot of people to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:42.46,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:44.97,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the people here have circumstances of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.97,0:04:48.30,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,It's not uncommon for us to have things we don't want others to hear, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:53.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's the kind of thing that could get me\Ncourt-martialed if people were to find out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.77,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I've done things of that caliber, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:04:58.19,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:01.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'll forgive us unless we tell her something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:03.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But Winry is practically a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.07,0:05:05.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.11,0:05:08.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave out the part about the\NFührer President and the Homunculi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.57,0:05:09.99,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What are you whispering on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:11.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:15.46,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess we can just tell her,\N"We're on a journey to get our bodies back".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.92,0:05:29.59,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why you're looking for a girl who carries this cat around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:32.51,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:34.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then will you help us-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:41.44,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I get you are scatterbrains who act without thinking and end up adding fuel to flames because of your carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:44.44,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to keep fools like you in my castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:49.45,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... why don't the higher-ups at Central keep fools like you chained up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.95,0:05:51.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Leave here at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:59.04,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I'd like to say, but I'm highly interested in Eastern Alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.04,0:06:02.96,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You two are acquainted with that girl from Xing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:04.96,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess you could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:07.30,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It's technology we don't have in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:08.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.80,0:06:11.35,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You can never have enough technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:15.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Especially in this land, where we frequently combat Drakma, a large nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.77,0:06:19.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how we apply it, Eastern Alchemy may become a useful combat tool for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.73,0:06:20.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:24.44,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Alchemy is especially versed in medicinal purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:24.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Using that for war-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:26.32,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Did I give you permission to speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:29.53,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You're nothing but dogs that do nothing but bark within the borders of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:35.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you forget for a second that you fools are living in peace because there exist those who protect the borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:38.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I am in charge of protecting the northern border.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:42.04,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If the technique would be useful to my duty, then I'll take it. Whatever it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:47.26,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the search for the little girl to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.76,0:06:49.88,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you two out of the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.18,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:53.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:55.39,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Give these two some work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.39,0:06:56.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.27,0:06:59.68,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"If a man will not work, he shall not eat."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:02.31,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Can't argue with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:07.19,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,They've got quite a rough history behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:13.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Although they seem to be fairly experienced in combat, I now know that they're just brats on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:15.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:19.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like they have some secrets they're not willing to share with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.38,0:07:31.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you going to make us do exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:38.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor said that a lot of people here have\Ncircumstances of their own. Does that go for you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:45.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you ask us about every detail of our lives,\Nand now you're ignoring us? Talk about unfair!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.19,0:07:49.44,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.03,0:07:55.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Red eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:56.20,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:57.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:02.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that all of the soldiers of Ishbalan descent were purged before the extermination...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:07.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I do have some Ishbalan blood in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.29,0:08:11.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,However, my grandmother, my father, and my wife do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.26,0:08:17.35,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,The colors of my skin and eyes came from my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:21.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Amestrian...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:25.60,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You sure had your way with\Nthe land of my ancestors, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:40.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You Ishbalans burned down my hometown, too, and even killed my friend's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:41.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:53.97,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.47,0:08:57.84,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're actually the first one who talked back after I said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:00.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You were testing me, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:01.89,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.35,0:09:07.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that people view me with pity after that civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:09.40,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I was getting sick of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:10.90,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But you were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:19.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've met Ishbalans who wanted to kill me, ones who tried to kidnap me, and others I've made peace with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So I've been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:29.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, I believe it's possible for individuals to be able to talk as equals without having to worry about race.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:43.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Were you enlisted in the military during the extermination, Major Miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.31,0:09:44.31,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:48.48,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I served as assistant to Major General Armstrong then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:52.19,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,The extermination began as soon as I was stationed here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:56.57,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,and all of my Ishbalan relatives, beginning with my grandfather, were killed in the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:10:00.99,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,My life was saved due to my narrowly missing the requirements of the purge statute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.53,0:10:03.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not come to despise the military?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.20,0:10:07.00,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You don't hesitate to ask anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:10.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I hate being ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:13.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize if I offended you in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:17.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,A State Alchemist being ignorant, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.14,0:10:24.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I did despise what the military did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:29.64,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And at the same time, I had doubts about the\NMajor General for keeping me as her assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:36.57,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,By having someone like me, a person with Ishbalan blood around, it could cause trouble with the soldiers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.82,0:10:42.03,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, the Major General didn't exile me,\Nso I turned on her in anger and demanded answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:47.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Briggs shall not fall, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:54.29,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Every soldier here must be strong and flexible, fulfilling my every command.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:58.84,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They must make up a sturdy army that would keep calm under all circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.47,0:11:03.18,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there's no time for racism.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:12.56,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Because the blood of many races runs through your veins,\Nyou view this country from many angles and with many values.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:19.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}Because I was born and raised an Amestrian, I need someone like you by my side for me to be able to stand at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:22.86,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Follow my command without complaint, Miles!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:25.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Perfectly logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:27.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention that her words carried no deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:35.46,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I proceeded to ask her, "Even then, what if the Ishbalan in me couldn't forgive the army and took over my mind?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:37.84,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think she responded to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:40.09,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:43.34,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'll accept a duel from you at any time, as a representative of the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:44.76,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:46.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What an evil woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:48.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It should be easy saying that with a battalion at her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:50.85,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fairly certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:52.98,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'll slice you up in a one-on-one duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:54.77,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,...her eyes were saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:03.20,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of the universal law at this base?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:05.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Survival of the fittest", was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.53,0:12:06.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:10.37,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ones without power will die,\Nand ones with power will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.37,0:12:14.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This is always true, under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:16.13,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:21.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There are no underlings, bosses, and no distinctions between race, ethnicities, and gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:28.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good example of the survival of the fittest concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.81,0:12:31.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You lived through it because you had good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.44,0:12:36.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the guys who were supposed to be removing the icicles loafed on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:38.11,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's your job now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:41.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell one of my men to give you\Na tour of the inside once you finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.03,0:12:47.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't reach that high!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:49.58,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:53.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Falman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.33,0:12:54.87,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Elric Brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:56.54,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:59.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Speak for yourself! I thought you were getting transferred to Northern Headquarters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:04.47,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually sent here from Northern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:06.51,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You were promoted to Second Lieutenant!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:07.47,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.68,0:13:10.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Congratulations on your promot-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:12.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you in charge of the icicles?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:16.06,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here working the duties of the enlisted...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.23,0:13:19.98,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like that'll be your last promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.15,0:13:21.86,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.65,0:13:27.32,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is the development lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:29.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what's {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.87,0:13:36.75,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,They're developing weapons using the best technology in the country under orders from Major General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even automails for combat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:40.04,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.04,0:13:41.17,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Let me show you something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:53.10,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is the lowest level of Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:55.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's really warm down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:56.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Totally different from how it is up at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:14:00.44,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The lifeline of the fortress is gathered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:04.98,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the top of the fortress is attacked,\Nthe central part underground will remain unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:08.57,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,Out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.82,0:14:10.62,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be milling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:11.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.95,0:14:14.20,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Bobby, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:15.41,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's this pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.42,0:14:22.46,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,This sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.67,0:14:26.88,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:27.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.38,0:14:30.97,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like... someone's digging.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.47,0:14:35.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the Drakmans are building\Nan underground passage beneath the fortress?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:37.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.89,0:14:40.10,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.60,0:14:42.73,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Really, what a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.19,0:14:46.32,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a drag, I could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:50.49,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,But dying is also a drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Solf J. Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:19.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He was badly injured on a freight train on the way here and was hospitalized at the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:22.23,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He requests that Briggs supports him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.69,0:15:26.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't the Crimson Alchemist serving in jail?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:30.24,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he was discharged.\NUnder orders from the Führer President.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.82,0:15:32.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like the sound of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:37.74,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Intruders, ma'am! From underground!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.04,0:15:39.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:56.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Homunculus!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:01.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.14,0:16:06.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So they knew we came up here to search for ways to fight against the Homunculi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.12,0:16:19.95,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fall asleep!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.75,0:16:24.17,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.17,0:16:26.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:29.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You heard about us from your Father at Central, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.42,0:16:30.96,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:35.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We just came here to search for ways to get our bodies back...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:37.35,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Who... are you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:41.56,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,I... have to dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:43.52,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.52,0:16:45.85,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Such a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:48.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, could it be that he...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.61,0:16:53.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maybe neither Father nor the\NFührer President have told him about us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.86,0:17:00.45,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard! So you {\i1}are{\i0\fscx30} {\r} spies from Drakma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.45,0:17:02.12,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,We're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.12,0:17:04.96,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you speaking to the intruder like you're friends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:06.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're not friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.79,0:17:07.83,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You can't trick me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:08.96,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,This is in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.96,0:17:10.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.71,0:17:11.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:21.97,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,There's... so much room here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.31,0:17:24.39,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:29.81,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Do I not have to dig anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.81,0:17:31.02,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:37.20,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Bullets are ineffective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.28,0:17:42.87,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where... am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.08,0:17:51.67,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! He's headed for the development lair!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:52.38,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:53.76,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Contact the men up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:17:55.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We need to go after him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:55.84,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:23.70,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,He's huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:28.33,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's... warm in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:29.50,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:39.30,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Put out the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:40.18,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:52.56,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I know I hit him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:54.69,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:56.94,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Bullets don't work against him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:58.07,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.86,0:19:00.95,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,All noncombatants are to withdraw immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.36,0:19:02.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Shut off the alarm, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:05.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let Drakma know about this commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:08.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought it, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:11.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Has it been tested?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:13.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:15.84,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's the proud of work of us developers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:18.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Remove the fuse from the shell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.05,0:19:19.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:31.31,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,First shell, loaded!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:32.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:36.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Bull's eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:46.16,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:54.21,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's a drag to feel pain, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:19:58.80,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just sit there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:19:59.55,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Load the next shell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.97,0:20:03.84,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.19,0:20:19.28,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:23.28,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I forgot about my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:27.20,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,I have to dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:48.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, General!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:50.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He won't die no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.85,0:20:52.10,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Won't die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.68,0:20:54.39,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:56.60,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know so much about that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:20:59.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I-I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.61,0:21:02.36,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like dilly-dalliers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.36,0:21:05.24,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Answer everything that you {\i1}can{\i0\fscx30} {\r} answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:08.16,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:09.58,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a spy from Drakma?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.74,0:21:10.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:12.87,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Then is that thing a spy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:14.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.42,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Does that thing know you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.42,0:21:18.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.17,0:21:20.25,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What {\i1}is{\i0\fscx30} {\r} that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:23.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Who is commanding him to act?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:27.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.43,0:21:29.89,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And why can't you answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.72,0:21:33.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Please try to realize...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:39.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,This is my last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:41.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Do you two plan to ally yourselves with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.23,0:21:44.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see the people here die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:48.66,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what his body is made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.45,0:21:53.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fairly certain his body structure and composition are identical to humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:56.21,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Identical to humans, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.87,0:22:01.25,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer, bring me some tank fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.25,0:22:02.42,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to pour it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.42,0:22:03.13,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.13,0:22:04.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, it's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.76,0:22:06.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you light him on fire, he won't...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.88,0:22:09.89,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I've already gathered from the\Nprevious attacks that he won't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.30,0:22:12.76,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll just shut off his bodily functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:15.64,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let him have something far worse than flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.69,0:22:22.98,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you how we do things at Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.70,0:24:00.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The bodies that clash against each other..
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.54,0:24:02.37,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The shells that explode in the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.62,0:24:06.88,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx90}The battle against the Homunculus threatening the North defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.88,0:24:11.22,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Will it be us who will win the battle? Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.05,0:24:16.01,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.01,0:24:19.64,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 35, The Shape of This Country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.64,0:24:22.60,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,All that stands in our way shall be annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.23,0:24:25.40,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That is the law of the North.
